cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.MS 

This paper deals with abstract interpretation and coinduction, which are topics related to logic and programming languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses abstract domains, which are used in program analysis and verification, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely category. The paper also touches on software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages (cs.FL), and mathematical software (cs.MS), which are all relevant sub-categories.
